[medium] src/views/system/DiagramsView.vue:285 (correctness vs. the actual SDK/library)
When the authorization-boundary diagram group fetch returns 404, fetchOptionalDiagram now swallows the error but leaves authorizationBoundary at its initialData value of { diagrams: [{ uuid: v4() }] }. That makes a missing optional group render a blank, never-created diagram with Save/Delete controls instead of the empty state, and subsequent PUT/DELETE calls target a diagram UUID the API never returned.
Suggested fix: On a swallowed 404, reset the corresponding diagram group to an empty object or empty diagrams array. For authorization-boundary specifically, remove the seeded blank diagram initialData or pass the group ref into fetchOptionalDiagram so 404 handling can set grouping.value = { diagrams: [] }.
Guidance: In src/views/system/DiagramsView.vue, the finding is valid: authorizationBoundary is initialized with { diagrams: [{ uuid: v4() }] }, and fetchOptionalDiagram() currently only swallows a 404 without clearing that seeded placeholder. Fix this locally in DiagramsView.vue by making 404 handling reset the corresponding diagram group ref to an empty diagrams array. A precise approach: change fetchOptionalDiagram to accept the target grouping ref, e.g. async function fetchOptionalDiagram(fetchDiagram: () => Promise<unknown>, grouping: Ref<Diagrammable | undefined>) { try { await fetchDiagram(); } catch (error) { const err = error as AxiosError; if (err.response?.status !== 404) throw error; grouping.value = { diagrams: [] } as Diagrammable; } }. Then update onMounted to call fetchOptionalDiagram(fetchAuthorizationBoundaryDiagram, authorizationBoundary as unknown as Ref<Diagrammable | undefined>), and similarly pass networkArchitecture and dataFlow. Preserve the deliberate design decision: only swallow 404s for these optional diagram group fetches; keep non-404 failures throwing. Do not remove the existing Add Diagram flow, createDiagram POST, save/delete URLs, or shared forms. If TypeScript complains about the useDataApi ref type, use the same Ref<Diagrammable | undefined> cast pattern already used in resolveGrouping().
